# =============================================================================
# Quackmaster → Supabase (browser client only)
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to `.env` for local dev (`npm run dev`). Never commit `.env`.
#
# GitHub Pages CI: add the SAME variable NAMES under
#   Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# (and/or Environment secrets for the `github-pages` environment).
#
# Where to copy values (Supabase Dashboard):
#   Your project → Project Settings → API
#
#   • Project URL     → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#     Example: https://abcdefghij.supabase.co
#
#   • Publishable key (recommended, prefix sb_publishable_…)
#       → VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
#     OR legacy “anon” “public” JWT (starts eyJ…)
#       → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# Use ONE client key variable — publishable wins if both are set.
#
# NEVER put these in the frontend bundle:
#   • service_role key / Secret API key (sb_secret_…)
# They bypass Row Level Security. Keep them server-side only.
# =============================================================================

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co

# New projects / Dashboard “Publishable” tab:
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# Legacy “anon” / “public” JWT (still supported by supabase-js):
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
